   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>SONNET.</head>
   <l>THe liuely Lampes of great Iehovaes licht</l>
   <l>Quhilk driues the deadly smoke of sin away</l>
   <l>The grounds of grace, the gage of glorie bright</l>
   <l>The way to wealth quhilk sall indure far ay.</l>
   <l>As Salue for saules, a solide plat to pray</l>
   <l>At morne, at nicht, and vther seasons mei<gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>
   </l>
   <l>A truth to <gap reason="illegible" resp="#tech" extent="1 word">
         <desc>〈◊〉</desc>
      </gap> the state where thou suld staye</l>
   <l>A healthsome hyue of heauenly songes sweit.</l>
   <l>Behald thou hes, in weichtie, wise, discreit</l>
   <l>And pleasant style, a schort and reddie way.</l>
   <l>To Paradyse with pleasures all repleit,</l>
   <l>To reigne and sing O holy, holy aye.</l>
   <l>Pray and assay herein sum space to spend.</l>
   <l>Giue place to grace, and God sall blesse the end.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>M. W. S.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
